Problem: In octagon $ABCDEFGH$, every side is perpendicular to each of its adjacent sides. What is the perimeter of $ABCDEFGH$?

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(10,0)--(10,6)--(6,6)--(6,2)--(2,2)--(2,10)--(0,10)--(0,0)--cycle,linewidth(2));

label("A",(0,10),W);
label("B",(0,0),W);
label("C",(10,0),E);
label("D",(10,6),NE);
label("E",(6,6),NW);
label("F",(6,2),SE);
label("G",(2,2),SW);
label("H",(2,10),NE);

label("10",(5,0),S);
label("6",(10,3),E);
label("4",(6,4),E);
label("8",(2,6),E);
[/asy]
Answer:

The octagon can be divided into 8 congruent right triangles by drawing a perpendicular from each vertex to the center of the octagon. Since all sides of the octagon have the same length, we can label the sides of each right triangle as shown below:

[asy]
pair A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H,O;
O=(0,0);
A=(0,10);
B=(0,0);
C=(10,0);
D=(10,6);
E=(6,6);
F=(6,2);
G=(2,2);
H=(2,10);
draw(A--B--C--D--E--F--G--H--cycle,linewidth(2));
draw(A--O);
draw(B--O);
draw(C--O);
draw(D--O);
draw(E--O);
draw(F--O);
draw(G--O);
draw(H--O);
label("$x$",(A+O)/2,NW);
label("$x$",(O+B)/2,SW);
label("$x$",(C+O)/2,SE);
label("$x$",(O+D)/2,NE);
label("$x$",(E+O)/2,NW);
label("$x$",(O+F)/2,SW);
label("$x$",(G+O)/2,SE);
label("$x$",(H+O)/2,NE);
label("$10$",(B+C)/2,S);
label("$6$",(C+D)/2,SE);
label("$4$",(E+F)/2,SW);
label("$8$",(G+H)/2,NW);
[/asy]

Using the Pythagorean theorem, we can find that $x^2 + 4^2 = 6^2$, so $x=2$. Similarly, $x^2 + 8^2 = 10^2$, so $x=6$. Thus, each side of the octagon has length $2+6+4+8=20$, and the perimeter of the octagon is $8 \times 20 = \boxed{160}$.

